15/02/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer arrived in Pristina Thursday (February 15th) for talks with Kosovo leaders, UNMIK head Joachim Ruecker and the commander of KFOR, Lieutenant General Roland Kather. He will also visit Mitrovica to meet with Kosovo Serb mayors. According to press reports, Scheffer voiced support for UN envoy Martti Ahtisaari's status plan and stressed that NATO would not allow violence in Kosovo. He condemned weekend clashes between pro-independence demonstrators and police, in which two people died and dozens were injured.
In other newsWednesday, Kosovo President Fatmir Sejdiu said he would wait until an investigation is completed before taking punitive action against police officials. The Skopje daily Dnevnik, meanwhile, reported that hundreds of ethnic Albanians from Macedonia participated in Saturday's rally. It said they came at the invitation of the Vetevendosje (Self-determination) movement, which staged the protest. (Glas javnosti - 16/02/07; NATO website, Tanjug, Dnevnik - 15/02/07; KosovaLive, KosovaPress.com, Focus - 14/02/07)
